headlines.description: David Efianayi scored four of his 19 points in the final 2:04 and Gardner-Webb held off Hampton 80-79 on Sunday.
Rodney Bullock made two free throws with 0.6 seconds left and Providence rallied to defeat Stony Brook 62-60 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bullock's free throws lift Providence over Stony Brook 62-60

headlines.description: Lamar Stevens scored 23 points and added 12 rebounds for his first career double-double, Mike Watkins added 14 points and 12 rebounds, and Penn State dominated George Mason in the post on its way to a 72-54 victory Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stevens, Watkins record double-doubles in Penn State victory

headlines.description: Bogdan Bliznyuk scored 16 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Eastern Washington returned home for the first time since Nov. 10 to snap a five-game losing streak with an 86-58 victory over Cal State Northridge on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bliznyuk, EWU beat Northridge 86-58, snap 5-game loss streak

headlines.description: Travis Reid matched his career-high with 29 points in helping Stanford win its third in four games, beating San Francisco 71-59 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reid scores 29 points in Stanford's 71-59 win over the Dons

headlines.description: Sheriff Drammeh finished with a career-high 20 points, including the go-ahead 3-pointer with 38 seconds to go to help Hawaii slip past Utah Valley 70-69 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Drammeh scores 20, including late 3; Hawaii tops Utah Valley

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
